<item>
            <title>[SPARK-12181] Check Cached unaligned-access capability before using Unsafe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-12181</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For MemoryMode.OFF_HEAP, Unsafe.getInt etc. are used with no restriction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the Oracle implementation uses these methods only if the class variable unaligned (commented as &quot;Cached unaligned-access capability&quot;) is true, which seems to be calculated whether the architecture is i386, x86, amd64, or x86_64.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should perform similar check for the use of Unsafe.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
